<div type="definition">
<p>DILIGENT so as to pay ATTENTION to EVEN UNIMPORTANT PARTS of something.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current general word for detail is xiáng 詳 (ant. lè 略 "without proper detail" and yào 要 "only in main outline").</p>
<p>2. Xì 細 (ant. hūn 涽 "in a muddled generalising way") refers to petty detail.</p>
<p>3. Xī 悉 refers to completeness of detail.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>仔細</p>
